      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While feeling better is a positive sign, it doesn't always mean all the bacteria have been eliminated, especially with antibiotics. Bacteria can persist even when visible symptoms disappear. Prematurely stopping the medication significantly increases the risk of a recurrence or developing antibiotic-resistant bacteria. It is best to discuss your severe stomach upset with your doctor, as they might be able to recommend a less harsh alternative or manage the side effects while you finish the treatment.",
      "source": "target",
