      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Taking a double dose or abruptly switching to supplements is not a safe substitute for completing the prescribed antibiotic course. Increasing the dose without medical instruction can be dangerous and may not be effective against the specific bacteria. High doses of Vitamin C and probiotics are not proven replacements for antibiotics and will not eradicate an active bacterial infection. Please prioritize following your doctor's instructions to properly clear your infection and avoid complications.",
      "source": "target",
